Build an enterprise-grade, multi-tenant web app.
Tech: React + Vite + TypeScript + Tailwind. No Next.js. No Remix.
Use a Mock API Service Layer that mimics backend contracts (so later we can replace with Spring Boot).
Keep all business logic in src/services/* and src/domain/* (no logic inside components).
Use Zustand (or Redux Toolkit) for app state; prefer Zustand for simplicity.
Use React Router for routing.
Use Zod for validation.
Use a consistent UI component library approach (either shadcn-like local components or simple Tailwind components).
Every feature must be dynamic/config-driven (JSON schemas, mappings, connector definitions).
Multi-tenancy: tenantId is required on all data models and service calls.
Correlation ID: system must support correlationId passed with each request; persist and use it for joins.